description:
Tony had felt from the beginning that he and Loki might have some (or many) similarities. The more time he spends with the God of Mischief, the more he realizes just how deep their similarities run.

A songfic exploring the relationship between two flawed people that have been hurt, and don’t know how to heal. The song this is based on is “Flaws” by Bastille.

title: Tell me I'm wrong

by S_Horne

“I worked it out! You’re in love! That’s why you’re so grumpy all of a sudden; it’s quite obvious that something’s wrong when Steve Rogers stops smiling. And that’s the reason that you have loads of ice cream and cookies in the kitchen instead of your usual health shit. You’re sulking. It has to be love because there’s nothing else that would get you down. The only thing would be one of your friends being hurt, but we’re all fine, so it has to be a you thing. And your job is perfect and your apartment is perfect and everything else is shipshape, so it’s gotta be your heart.”

summary: Side Effects May Include (Tony Stark x Daughter)
title: Side Effects May Include (Tony Stark x Daughter)
body:
Side Effects May Include (Masterlist)

Part 5

Warnings: None that i can Think of… 

Word Count: 1,087

Credit to all the gif owners! 




“Dad, if you’re going to pester me with questions about tonight, acting as if you didn’t trust me then why did you ask me to go in the first place?” I asked I put my earrings on.

“it isn’t that I don’t trust you, it’s just I want it to go perfect and I’m not there to make sure it does..”

“So, you don’t trust me.”

“Is that really all you heard?” He takes one look at my outfit, “those shoes?”

“What about them?” I asked looking at my flats.

“Maybe heels, it’s a bit more stylish,” he walks over to my closet and begins to rummage through, “These black heels would be nice.”

“I can barely walk in those! And who has to go to this thing anyway? Me. That’s who.”

“Yes, but you have to make a good impression on my behalf.” I sigh and grab the heels from his hands, “don’t expect me to be dancing tonight… and don’t expect any other favors like this ever again,” I said as I took off my flats and placed on my heels.

Dad grinned and kissed my forehead, “I won’t.” He smiles, “You look gorgeous. Are you staying at Jasmine’s tonight?” I nod, “Alright, well, happy will be dropping you off at the party, you know to call him if you girls need a ride and to call me if anything and…” he sighs, “Be safe. If you’re going to drink be responsible.”

“Dad.”

“Let me finish, don’t smoke, okay?”

“Dad, you give me this small lecture every time I go to a party and I’ve always been fine.” He nods, “I got this.”

“I know.”


 ~ Time Skip ~ 

“I don’t understand as to why you wanted me to drop you off an hour late,” Happy said as we pulled up to the mansion, where the party is being held.

“I’m not late, everyone is simply just an hour early. Plus, given the fact that Tony Stark is my dad, I always have to make a grand entrance.”

Happy lets out a small sigh and smiles, “That you are.”

I got off of the car, thanking Happy. Walking into the mansion, “name?” I heard someone say.

I turned to see a guy in a black suit, “Olivia Stark.”

He looks at a list and nods, “I will inform Mr. Johnson that you have arrived.” He holds the door open for me, I thank him and walked right in. I quickly took in my surroundings, I felt like a small fish in the ocean.

I right away knew I had to get myself a drink to stop myself from looking at my phone for some sort of distraction, I walked over to the bar and ordered myself a coke. The bartender acted surprised when I had said, “Coke,” as if he were expecting me to order an alcoholic beverage.

I looked over to the dance floor and noticed Bren walking over to me, “you must be Bren.”

“You must be Olivia Stark,” He smiled, “Daughter of Tony Stark, also known as one of the men on my dad’s most hated list.”

I smirked, “My dad and I are two different people, although we carry very similar traits and well, DNA of course, his mistakes are not mine. I do, want to personally thank you for the invitation.”

“You were highly spoken of by some of my dad’s closest companions, it would’ve been a shame to not invite you, although, given the fact that my dad wasn’t too delighted that the company of a stark would be at my parties, I still had to have you here.”

I looked around, “your party is very different from the parties I have attended.”

“Yes, well, I have a reputation to make. Especially with someone like my father, I have big plans in my future. Ones that I can not achieve with parties that are like… high school parties.”

“Don’t you find it sad that we have to live up to these expectations because of our parents?” I asked as I grabbed the drink that was placed for me on the counter. He escorted me to a small booth, we both sat down as I began to take a sip of my drink.

“I find it sad that some people think it’s right to steal other peoples ideas.”

“Ideas or suggestions. People should really label things if they really cared for them.”

He pursed his lips together, “now-now, Livia, we all know your father did mine dirty.”

“Nothing personal, but that’s life.”  I chuckled, “Don’t you think it’s silly that we’re arguing over something that happened between our parents and not us?” I asked as I placed my drink on the table.

He chuckled, “you’re right, it is silly. But we’re doing their dirty work for them.”

I nod, “Does this mean you’ll put in a good word for me then?”

“We’ll see,” he smirks.

“We’ll see?”

He nods, “Refill?” Before I could protest, he grabbed my glass and walked away. I was then left alone to watch as people danced to the music, I looked for Liam, spotting him on the dance floor with a girl. It looked like the girl he had talked about, the one he had his eye on for a while and from the looks of the way they were dancing it looked like he finally grew the balls to ask her out or something of the sort.

Before I knew it, Bren came back with my drink, I took a small glance at my watch to see that he had taken longer than I expected. I looked over to where Liam was but I couldn’t find him,  “It would be a shame if you came to this party only to talk business,” he began to say as he glanced to the crowd of people dancing, “you should at least attempt to have some fun.”

“Is this your attempt to ask me to dance with you?” He laughs, “because it’s a horrible one.”

He smiles, “well, will you?”

“One dance won’t hurt,” I said softly as I took a sip of my drink before getting up. Everything about the taste of the drink felt off, I looked over at Bren who was smiling at me as he held out his arm for me to take. Maybe I’m just thinking way too much about it. I grabbed his arm and he led me to the dance floor. I wish I had listened to my gut feeling.



Taglist: @waves-and-sunflowers @spiderlingsweb @emmii4 @henrietteoaks @spider-woman22 @abitofeverythinggg @oliolioxiclean @littlephoenix-fire

“Yes, well, I have a reputation to make. Especially with someone like my father, I have big plans in my future. Ones that I can not achieve with parties that are like… high school parties.”

“Don’t you find it sad that we have to live up to these expectations because of our parents?” I asked as I grabbed the drink that was placed for me on the counter. He escorted me to a small booth, we both sat down as I began to take a sip of my drink.

“I find it sad that some people think it’s right to steal other peoples ideas.”

“Ideas or suggestions. People should really label things if they really cared for them.”

He pursed his lips together, “now-now, Livia, we all know your father did mine dirty.”

“Nothing personal, but that’s life.”  I chuckled, “Don’t you think it’s silly that we’re arguing over something that happened between our parents and not us?” I asked as I placed my drink on the table.

He chuckled, “you’re right, it is silly. But we’re doing their dirty work for them.”

I nod, “Does this mean you’ll put in a good word for me then?”

“We’ll see,” he smirks.

“We’ll see?”

He nods, “Refill?” Before I could protest, he grabbed my glass and walked away. I was then left alone to watch as people danced to the music, I looked for Liam, spotting him on the dance floor with a girl. It looked like the girl he had talked about, the one he had his eye on for a while and from the looks of the way they were dancing it looked like he finally grew the balls to ask her out or something of the sort.

Before I knew it, Bren came back with my drink, I took a small glance at my watch to see that he had taken longer than I expected. I looked over to where Liam was but I couldn’t find him,  “It would be a shame if you came to this party only to talk business,” he began to say as he glanced to the crowd of people dancing, “you should at least attempt to have some fun.”

“Is this your attempt to ask me to dance with you?” He laughs, “because it’s a horrible one.”

He smiles, “well, will you?”

“One dance won’t hurt,” I said softly as I took a sip of my drink before getting up. Everything about the taste of the drink felt off, I looked over at Bren who was smiling at me as he held out his arm for me to take. Maybe I’m just thinking way too much about it. I grabbed his arm and he led me to the dance floor. I wish I had listened to my gut feeling.

“You must be Olivia Stark,” He smiled, “Daughter of Tony Stark, also known as one of the men on my dad’s most hated list.”

I smirked, “My dad and I are two different people, although we carry very similar traits and well, DNA of course, his mistakes are not mine. I do, want to personally thank you for the invitation.”

“You were highly spoken of by some of my dad’s closest companions, it would’ve been a shame to not invite you, although, given the fact that my dad wasn’t too delighted that the company of a stark would be at my parties, I still had to have you here.”

He pursed his lips together, “now-now, Livia, we all know your father did mine dirty.”

“Nothing personal, but that’s life.”  I chuckled, “Don’t you think it’s silly that we’re arguing over something that happened between our parents and not us?” I asked as I placed my drink on the table.

He chuckled, “you’re right, it is silly. But we’re doing their dirty work for them.”

I nod, “Does this mean you’ll put in a good word for me then?”

“We’ll see,” he smirks.

“We’ll see?”

He nods, “Refill?” Before I could protest, he grabbed my glass and walked away. I was then left alone to watch as people danced to the music, I looked for Liam, spotting him on the dance floor with a girl. It looked like the girl he had talked about, the one he had his eye on for a while and from the looks of the way they were dancing it looked like he finally grew the balls to ask her out or something of the sort.

Before I knew it, Bren came back with my drink, I took a small glance at my watch to see that he had taken longer than I expected. I looked over to where Liam was but I couldn’t find him,  “It would be a shame if you came to this party only to talk business,” he began to say as he glanced to the crowd of people dancing, “you should at least attempt to have some fun.”

“Is this your attempt to ask me to dance with you?” He laughs, “because it’s a horrible one.”

He smiles, “well, will you?”

“One dance won’t hurt,” I said softly as I took a sip of my drink before getting up. Everything about the taste of the drink felt off, I looked over at Bren who was smiling at me as he held out his arm for me to take. Maybe I’m just thinking way too much about it. I grabbed his arm and he led me to the dance floor. I wish I had listened to my gut feeling.
